Package: flexss
Type: Package
Title: Fitting Flexible Subject-specific Curves
Version: 0.1.0
Author: Kenyon Ng
Maintainer: Kenyon Ng <work@kenyon.xyz>
Description: This is a R package for fitting flexible subject-specific curves
    when analysing longitudinal data. Currently, it implements a Bayesian
    semiparametric model which allows modelling subject-specific curves as
    splines.
License: MIT + file LICENSE
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
RoxygenNote: 7.1.1
Depends:
    R (>= 2.10)
Imports: 
    stats,
    methods,
    MASS,
    Matrix,
    purrr
Suggests: 
    testthat (>= 3.0.0),
    magrittr,
    stringr,
    dplyr,
    withr,
    bayesplot
Config/testthat/edition: 3
Config/testthat/parallel: true
